		<tr>
						<td valign="top" width="100%" class="article_column">
				
<table class="contentpaneopen">
<tr>
		<td class="contentheading" width="100%">
					Tamama			</td>
	
	
		<td align="right" width="100%" class="buttonheading">
	<a href="/index.php?view=article&amp;catid=53%3Abooks&amp;id=93%3Atamama&amp;tmpl=component&amp;print=1&amp;page=&amp;option=com_content&amp;Itemid=73" title="Print" onclick="window.open(this.href,'win2','status=no,toolbar=no,scrollbars=yes,titlebar=no,menubar=no,resizable=yes,width=640,height=480,directories=no,location=no'); return false;"><img src="/images/M_images/printButton.png" alt="Print"  /></a>	</td>
	
		<td align="right" width="100%" class="buttonheading">
	<a href="/index.php?option=com_mailto&amp;tmpl=component&amp;link=aHR0cDovL3d3dy5wb250aWFuZ3JlZWtzLm9yZy9pbmRleC5waHA/dmlldz1hcnRpY2xlJmlkPTkzJTNBdGFtYW1hJm9wdGlvbj1jb21fY29udGVudCZJdGVtaWQ9NzM=" title="E-mail" onclick="window.open(this.href,'win2','width=400,height=300,menubar=yes,resizable=yes'); return false;"><img src="/images/M_images/emailButton.png" alt="E-mail"  /></a>	</td>
		   </tr>
</table>
<table class="contentpaneopen">




<tr>
<td valign="top" colspan="2">
<p align="center"><a title="" target="_blank" href="/images/media_files/media/tamama-front-cover.jpg"><img title="Click to enlarge image" style="margin-bottom: 5px; width: 210px; margin-right: 7px; height: 273px" alt="Click to enlarge image" src="/images/media_files/media/tamama-front-cover.jpg" width="100" align="bottom" border="0" height="136" /></a></p>
<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'"><font size="2" color="#000000" face="Arial"><font color="#000000">The Pontian Greek Society of Chicago has a limited supply of the powerful book <em>Tamama-The Missing Girl of Pontos </em>written by George Andreadis</font>.&nbsp;</font></span><a title="" target="_self" href="/index.php?option=com_contact&amp;view=contact&amp;id=2&amp;Itemid=65"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(137, 14, 6); font-family: 'Calibri','sans-serif'; text-decoration: none"><font face="Arial">Contact us</font></span></a><span><font face="Arial"><font size="3"><font color="#000000"><font size="2">&nbsp;<font color="#000000">to receive a copy of the book with your <strong>US$15</strong>&nbsp;donation to our organization.&nbsp;<br />
</font></font><br />
</font></font><font color="#000000"><font size="2"><strong>Quote from the book:</strong></font><br />
<br /></font></font></span><span><font size="2"><font face="Arial"><font color="#000000"><em>Sometimes Symela used to tell the story of her childhood years to her children. She used to tell them about Espye, about Papayiannis and about her mother Kyriaki. She told of her suffering in exile with tears in her eyes, up to the time when she had lost her father, mother and her brother Alekos. She never spoke of her sister Tamama. None of the children had ever heard anything about her.<br />
</em><br />
</font></font></font></span><span><font size="2"><font face="Arial"><font color="#000000"><strong>About the author:<br />
</strong><br />
</font></font></font></span><span><font size="2" color="#000000" face="Arial">George Andreadis was born in the refugee huts of Kalamaria in 1936. His parents came from Batum to Kalamaria in the 1930s. His father, Kyriakos Andreadis, was a Member of Parliament of Independent Pontos in Batum. <br />
<br /></font></span><span><font size="2"><font face="Arial"><font color="#000000">Mr. Andreadis graduated from Anatolia College in Thessaloniki, where he attended on a scholarship. He then studied Political Economy at the University of Freiburg in Germany. He speaks German and English. <br />
<br />Since childhood, he has been interested in everything to do with Pontos and the Pontians. He has visited the Black Sea more than 35 times. He is actively associated with the Pontians of the Black Sea and the Pontic Organizations of Greece and other continents. He has written various articles about Pontos, unpublished as of yet. In 1960, he published his book <em>The Civilization of Pontos</em>.</font> &nbsp;
<o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>
<p><font size="2" face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></p></td>
</tr>



